    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <h3>What is the rated capacity of the Alfa Laval NX 418 decanter centrifuge?</h3>
    <p>The Alfa Laval NX 418 B31-G two-phase decanter centrifuge has a rated capacity of 110 GPM on water sludge thickening. The three-phase UVNX 418 variant has a rated capacity of 70 GPM on fish stickwater and fishmeal separation.</p>

    <h3>What is the difference between the NX 418 and UVNX 418 decanter centrifuges?</h3>
    <p>The NX 418 is a two-phase <a href="/decanter-centrifuge/">decanter centrifuge</a> designed for liquid-solid separation such as sludge thickening and dewatering. The UVNX 418 is a <a href="/three-phase-decanter/">three-phase decanter</a> (tricanter) designed for liquid-liquid-solid separation applications such as fish oil, olive oil, and animal fat rendering. Learn more about the <a href="/difference-between-decanter-centrifuge-disc-centrifuge/">difference between decanter and disc centrifuges</a>.</p>

